Title: Non-commutative Oscillators and the commutative limit
Authors: B.Muthukumar and P.Mitra
Comments: Latex, 6 pages, Minor changes and references added
Journal-ref: Phys.Rev. D66 (2002) 027701
\\
  It is shown in first order perturbation theory that anharmonic oscillators in
non-commutative space behave smoothly in the commutative limit just as harmonic
oscillators do. The non-commutativity provides a method for converting a
problem in degenerate perturbation theory to a non-degenerate problem.
